Hello {{ user.first_name }},

Welcome to Metalab! Thank you for your support – we hope you will have a lot of fun, realise cool projects and make new friends.

We have accepted your membership application and created a user account for you in Metalab OS (MOS).

Your login details are as follows:
Account name: {{ user.username }}
We have set a temporary password for you. Please reset your password as soon as possible: https://metalab.at/member/password_reset/

Once you have set your password, please log in immediately and check your details. If we made a mistake when copying from the membership form, please reply to this email with the correction so that we can adjust the data!

You can log in to MOS at the top right of https://metalab.at/mos. You can also find your profile at https://metalab.at/member/{{ user.username }}/. With your account, you can change your user data and create events at the Metalab calendar. In MOS, you can also add an avatar for yourself, which will then be displayed on the main page via a random generator. (Please make sure that the image is not too large and square, otherwise it will be distorted.)

{% if user.paymentinfo.bank_account_mandate_reference %}
With your consent, we will debit your membership fee from your specified account in the middle of the month under the mandate ID {{ user.paymentinfo.bank_account_mandate_reference }}.{% endif %}
If you have ticked the checkbox for the internal mailing list, you will be subscribed. As the name suggests, many Metalab internal matters are discussed on this list. In addition, there are public mailing lists, find out more about other lists here: https://metalab.at/wiki/Mailinglisten

If you have checked the box for the internal Matrix channel, you will be invited to the room automatically, which is intended as a chat equivalent to the internal mailing list.
It would also be great if you could drop by the public Matrix space (https://matrix.to/#/#metalab-space:matrix.org), where topics from Metalab are regularly discussed in various rooms.

If you would like an account on our wiki (https://metalab.at/wiki/), reply to this email and we will create one for you. On your user page, you can add a more detailed description of yourself and your interests.

If you have any questions or problems concerning purely administrative matters, you can contact the core team at core@metalab.at. All other questions, ideas, etc. concerning Metalab are better addressed on the internal channels.

As a member of Metalab, you have responsibilities and rights. Much of this might be self-evident, but we have summarised these responsibilities and rights here:

Rights:
* Use of the infrastructure (in the case of machines and tools, please only if you have the appropriate technical knowledge and skills or after training)
* Use of the kitchen (with special attention to clearing away dishes and keeping the kitchen clean in general; food is disposed of during the daily clean-up at 8 p.m.)
* Right to have a say at the fortnightly Jour Fixe (https://metalab.at/wiki/Jour_Fixe)
* Participation in the social plenum (https://metalab.at/wiki/Sozialplenum) to discuss all community related topics at Metalab (topics only visible after Wiki login)
* Voting rights at the annual general meeting and any extraordinary general meetings
* Reservation of Metalab rooms for free and topic-related workshops or lectures by entering them in the calendar: https://metalab.at/calendar/ (if you are unsure, please ask Core)

Once we have got to know you a little better and you have actively and positively participated in activities at Metalab, you will also have the opportunity to obtain a key (iButton) for completely independent access to the lab. To do so, please first attend a Keymember workshop (https://metalab.at/wiki/Keymember_Workshop) and then apply for the key at a social plenum meeting.

Responsibilities:
* Paying your membership fee on time
* Complying with the house rules (Code of Conduct, https://metalab.at/wiki/Code_of_Conduct/en)
* Complying with the exclusive days (https://metalab.at/wiki/Exklusive_Tage)
* Helping to keep the lab clean and tidy
* Leaving your workspace clean and tidy
* Independently maintaining and cleaning shared areas, even if you are not responsible for the mess (e.g. loading/unloading the dishwasher, clearing away empty drinks bottles, restocking the fridge, taking bin bags to the bin room, see http://metalab.at/wiki/Umgebung, general assistance with the 10-minute clean-up at 8 p.m., etc.)

It is also appreciated if you participate in the communal life at Metalab and show commitment.

If you need further information, you can either speak to other members directly and/or search the Metalab wiki: https://metalab.at/wiki/

With kind regards,
Your Metalab.

